A rogue broker risked billions on the undervalued
A fraud of the heart.
That's what the French banking giant Société Générale, owner of the Commercial Bank of France, calls his shy employee Jerome Kerviel.
She lost almost five billion euros because of him.
But it seems that Kerviel was just a great player who wanted to match his teammates and certainly not incompetent.
Unlike all the big banking houses, he spotted the crisis in the U.S. mortgage market early.
"He's mentally weak", his superiors said, sending the police after him.
