What kind of insurance is right for me?
Car insurance, which protects the driver in the event of an accident, represents a considerable expense, which depends on various factors such as age, condition, gender, length of driving licence, type of vehicle to be insured or its use, etc.
Having a car is just the beginning.
Choosing the right car insurance is even more difficult than choosing a car model.
First, we need to figure out what we're talking about.
Car insurance is an agreement between the insurance company and the policyholder.
This obligation takes the form of an insurance contract which provides that the insurer will receive an agreed amount of insurance for taking on the liability for damages in the event of an insured event.
The insurance premium is the price of the insurance, which is determined by taking into account various factors such as age, status, sex, length of holding of the driving licence, type of vehicle being insured or its use, etc.
Insurance companies base their prices on statistics, so the higher the probability of an accident, the higher the insurance rate.
For this reason, both people over 25 and women have to pay lower premiums, as statistics show that they have a lower risk index due to their caution.
Similarly, on the basis of controls, insurance companies have concluded that married persons have fewer accidents than single drivers.
The way the vehicle is used will affect the frequency of the ride and thus the likelihood of an accident.
The more frequent the rides, the more likely they are.
There are many variables that insurance companies consider when setting the price of insurance premiums.
The driver must therefore study the situation carefully in order to choose the insurance that best suits his insured profile.
We will show you the most important variables for choosing this or that type of insurance, which will not only suit the type of insured but will also be reasonably priced.
People under 25 face various disadvantages, such as little driving experience and short driving licence periods, when they want to buy insurance at an affordable price.
Although all-hazard insurance is ideal for good cover, there are cheaper options.
The most cautious drivers can opt for all-risk insurance with a discount to get all-risk coverage, but at a more affordable price.
This type of contract would involve the client's participation in the payment of the insurance event.
'The part of the event that the client will pay will be determined in advance when determining the price of the policy, which will be higher the lower the participation rate,' explains Luis Noguera, CEO of First Europe in Spain, an online insurance intermediary.
The other option is insurance extended to other road users by insuring the client against damage caused to other persons but not against damage to his own car.
In addition, it would be insured against theft, fire and loss of the vehicle.
The references.
If you are under 25, try to be careful and avoid accidents as much as possible, as this will affect your bonus and allow you to reduce your premiums in the future.
The bonus is a reduction in the basic rate that the insurance company has.
On the contrary, the malus is an increase in the basic rate mentioned.
"Bonus and minus will depend on the insurance company and its profits.
If the insurance company has had a good year, it will be able to afford to increase the bonus", explains Noguera.
After the age of 25, it is easier for drivers to get insurance because the client risk index is reduced by the experience gained.
For this reason, it is most advisable to take out all-hazard insurance with a discount.
"Young people are usually unable to use the experience they have gained in advance at the time of the accident, even when driving", assures the director of the European company in Spain, adding that most accidents occur in the second year of driving, when the "fear of a beginner" has already been overcome.
However, if the client is married but has no children, it is better to take out all-hazard insurance, if his financial situation permits.
Families with children are considered by insurance companies as the clients with the lowest risk index and therefore their premiums will be lower.
In this case, the best insurance would be all-risk insurance with a premium discount (which could be EUR 300) or, with a high bonus, insurance extended to other road users, starting from the third year after the purchase of the vehicle.
"They drive more calmly and have a higher purchasing power, so they can afford the luxury of the highest discount", notes Luis Noguera.
Pensioners are advised to take out all-risk insurance with a discount on the premium (EUR 150) or extended to other operators if a high bonus has been achieved.
It must be said that car insurance is important not only because it protects the driver in the event of an accident but also because it represents a considerable expense, which is good reason to properly examine the insurance options that would suit us best in view of our personal situation.
