The Controller said the Scottish NHS Chambers must improve criminal record checks on non-European staff.
The recommendation from the President of the High Authority for Control Robert Black came after a foreign doctor operating in Scotland was linked to the June attacks at Glasgow Airport.
Mr Black is also concerned that the Scottish NHS does not have an accurate idea of the number of foreign staff it employs.
But his report stressed that the other key controls were all fine on a sample of five health authorities.
The President of the High Authority was concerned immediately after the June attacks at Glasgow Airport about personnel recruited from countries outside the European Economic Area.
